        "heading_pfkgD6": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Design, production, and testing of Sereluna period panties",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "text_iLeDDg": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Sereluna respects women's bodies and the environment. Our products are innovative, durable, and ethically made.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        },
        "feature_38b3Uk": {
          "type": "feature",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Design and sourcing",
            "text": "<p>We design our period panties ourselves. All our designs are original and unique. We source our raw materials directly from Western Europe and use organic cotton along with OEKO-TEX® Standard 100 certified fabrics and knits — only the best for your most sensitive area. Our packaging is made from FSC-certified paper.</p>"
          }
        },
        "feature_xtDfK6": {
          "type": "feature",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Manufacturing",
            "text": "<p>We do not use harmful chemicals such as nanosilver or PFAS in our period panties. Our products were tested for PFAS by TÜV in April 2023, and the results confirm that Sereluna period panties do not contain PFAS.</p>"
          }
        },
        "feature_BENM7d": {
          "type": "feature",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Testing",
            "text": "<p>Period panties are technically advanced and cannot be mass-produced by machines. Ours are handmade in Albania. The factory we work with undergoes an SMETA audit conducted by Intertek. The audit covers labor standards, health and safety, environmental practices, and business ethics. The results show zero non-conformities and zero observations, along with several best-practice examples.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
